Translate reward points removal message (aheadworks/module-reward-points >= 2.6.0).

Root cause: In 2.6.x the "were successfully removed" success message is built with
the `$t` alias (`mage/translate`) instead of the canonical `$.mage.__` translate call:

    message = $t('%1 were successfully removed.').replace('%1', rewardPointsLabelName);

`$.mage.__` (regex REGEX_MAGE_TRANSLATE) is collected into the JS translation
dictionary by every Magento version's `i18n:collect-phrases` parser, whereas the
`$t(...)` form (REGEX_TRANSLATE_FUNCTION) is only recognized by newer parser
versions, so the phrase is not reliably extracted and the message stays untranslated.

Fix: use `$.mage.__` while keeping the upstream `%1` placeholder so the static phrase
`'%1 were successfully removed.'` is translatable and the label is substituted after
translation.

Note: This supersedes fix-translate-remove-reward-points.patch for 2.6.x. That patch
targets the pre-2.6 source (`$t(rewardPointsLabelName + ' were successfully removed.')`)
which no longer exists here, so it is constrained to < 2.6.0.

diff --git a/view/frontend/web/js/action/remove-reward-points.js b/view/frontend/web/js/action/remove-reward-points.js
--- a/view/frontend/web/js/action/remove-reward-points.js
+++ b/view/frontend/web/js/action/remove-reward-points.js
@@ -31,7 +31,7 @@ define(

         action = function (rewardPointsLabelName) {
             var url = urlManager.getRemoveRewardPointsUrl(),
-                message = $t('%1 were successfully removed.').replace('%1', rewardPointsLabelName);
+                message = $.mage.__('%1 were successfully removed.').replace('%1', rewardPointsLabelName);

             messageContainer.clear();
